-- John Lewis Says Weekly Sales Increased 12 Percent on Electronics, Clothes
-- B y   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r
-- 2010-11-21T12:45:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-21/john-lewis-says-weekly-sales-increased-12-percent-on-electronics-clothes.html
John Lewis Partnership said weekly
sales at its U.K. department stores rose 12 percent from the
year-ago period, driven by Kindle e-book readers, Apple iPads
and beds.  Sales were 88 million pounds ($141 million) in the week to
Nov. 20, the London-based company said in an e-mailed statement
today. The figure is a 14 percent increase from the previous
week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dick Schumacher in London at 
